claim.claim-text:
1. A method for conducting a secure wireless sales transaction, comprising: 
receiving from a wireless transceiver device print identification data for an individual wanting to make a purchase; 
sending the print identification data to an identity verification service; 
sending transaction data about the purchase to a credit/debit financial service; 
obtaining verification data about the individual's identity and authorization to make the purchase using a particular credit account; and 
making a determination whether to complete the purchase based on the obtained verification data.
